cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with adapting a general parser to a sublanguage, which is a natural language processing task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of lexicon and morpho-guessing module extensions, which are common techniques in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method to reduce the complexity of text parsing using terminology, which can be seen as an AI approach. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with parsing texts in biology, which can be seen as an information retrieval task. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch on ethical considerations related to the use of natural language processing in biology.
